citeinfo.title: Zoning Districts (Base)

descript.abstract: This dataset represents base zoning districts of Atlanta, Georgia. Zoning is the primary method by which the City regulates land use in order to promote the public welfare. Each zoning district has its own set of permitted land uses as defined in the City of Atlanta Zoning Ordinance (Part 16 of the Code of Ordinances). The base zoning districts are designated as "base" because they do not include the representation of related mechanisms of regulated land use that apply to certain parts of the City and that are defined in the Zoning Ordinance: overlay zoning districts, special use permits, special administrative permits, variances, landmark buildings and sites, and historic buildings and sites.
descript.purpose: The base zoning districts data set is a major element of the official zoning map of the City and is used in a variety of computer applications to help City staff determine the allowed uses of a property for purposes such as issuing building permits and reviewing proposed land subdivision.
